radiographic_examinations.findings: Multiple tiny hypodensities throughout the liver; gallbladder partially distended without wall edema; mild dilation of the common bile duct; multiple tiny hypodensities throughout the kidneys likely representing cysts; inflammatory changes surrounding multiple sigmoid diverticula; focal bowel wall thickening in the left lower quadrant; mild wall thickening and mucosal hyperemia in mid-transverse colon; ovoid heterogeneous lesion centrally within the uterus; layering free fluid in the pelvis; lumbar dextroscoliosis.
